<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-08-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-08-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="729" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d729">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Walter S.
                                    Robertson</persName> to General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-08-03">3 August 1946</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>6407. Reurad 1224.<note n="32" xml:id="d729fn32">August 1, <ref target="#pg_1437">p. 1437</ref>.</note> A 3-way agreement has
                            been signed for the immediate dispatch of a fact-finding team to
                            investigate and report <pb facs="1455" n="1443" xml:id="pg_1443"/> upon
                            the ambush of Marine convoy on the Peiping–Tientsin road, 29 July. Field
                            Team 25 has been selected for this mission. Colonel M. F. Davis former
                            general officer who has had broad experience as chairman Team 7 is
                            designated as U. S. member and team chairman.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>